This system is designed using gRPC communication. It consists of 4 independent
services:
   Temperature Monitoring Service
   Humidity Monitoring Service
   Wire fire Risk Evaluation Service
   Fire Emergency Response Service
In this system, a central controller continuously collects real-time datas fromon-sitesensors and evaluates environmental conditions. 
When the wildfire risk values at alocation are exceeded, the controller automatically triggers emergency response service. FUNCTIONALITIES:
Temperature Monitoring Service
  Controller collects real-time temperature data from sensors. 
  Streams data continuously to the central controller.
  Provides latest temperature values on request (Unary). 
Humidity Monitoring Service
  Controller collects real-time temperature data from sensors. 
  Streams data continuously to the central controller. 
  Provides latest humidity values on request (Unary). 
Risk Evaluation Service (Central Controller)
  Receives environmental snapshots from temperature and humidity services. 
  Evaluates wildfire risk (LOW, MEDIUM, HIGH, CRITICAL). 
  Sends commands to Fire Emergency Service. 
Fire Emergency Response Service
  Receives commands from central controller. 
  Activates on-site sprinklers (Unary). Optional: continuous fire prevention devices status feedback (Bi-directional).
